Marie A. PROCTOR, Commissioner of Immigration, at Seattle, Wash., Appellant, v. WONG KIM YUEN, Appellee. No. 8440. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 23, 1937. J. Charles Dennis, U. S. Atty., and F. A. Pellegrini, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. Adam Beeler and Edwards E. Merges, both of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
